From their first match in 2006 to their final match in 2008, fifteen players represented the [[United States Virgin Islands cricket team]] in [[Twenty20]] (T20) matches in the [[Stanford 20/20]].<ref name="APPS">{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/individual/most_matches_career.html?class=6;id=47;type=team |title= Records / United States Virgin Islands / Twenty20 matches / Most matches |publisher=[[ESPNcricinfo]] |accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> A Twenty20 match is a [[cricket]] match between two representative teams of one twenty [[over (cricket)|over]] innings per side.<ref>{{cite journal|title=ICC Classification of Official Cricket|url=https://pulse-static-files.s3.amazonaws.com/ICC/document/2017/09/24/4510678a-e031-4a9b-a402-397d4868adb6/ICC-Classification-of-Official-Cricket-Effective-1st-October-2017.pdf|page=[https://pulse-static-files.s3.amazonaws.com/ICC/document/2017/09/24/4510678a-e031-4a9b-a402-397d4868adb6/ICC-Classification-of-Official-Cricket-Effective-1st-October-2017.pdf#page=6 6]|format=pdf|publisher=[[International Cricket Council]]|date=1 October 2017|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref>

The United States Virgin Islands has fielded a representative team since at least 1991.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Teams/3/3021/Other_Matches.html|title=Other Matches played by United States Virgin Islands|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> In regional domestic cricket, the United States Virgin Islands plays as part of the [[Leeward Islands cricket team]], which holds [[first-class cricket|first-class]], [[List A cricket|List A]] (neither of which the United States Virgin Islands has ever held) and Twenty20 status. However, for the [[Stanford 20/20]], islands in the [[Caribbean]] were allowed to play as separate teams, allowing the United States Virgin Islands the chance to compete with its own team in the [[Stanford 20/20#2006 tournament|2006 tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/westindies/content/story/223214.html|title=The Stanford Plan|last=Baksh|first=Vaneisa|date=27 October 2005|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> The United States Virgin Islands played two matches in the tournament, defeating [[Sint Maarten national cricket team|Sint Maarten]] by 47 runs in their preliminary round match,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/99/99949.html|title=St Maarten v United States Virgin Islands, 2006 Stanford 20/20|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> before losing in the first round to [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines national cricket team|St Vincent and the Grenadines]] by 5 wickets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/99/99954.html|title=St Vincent and the Grenadines v United States Virgin Islands, 2006 Stanford 20/20|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> Two years later, the United States Virgin Islands took part in the [[Stanford 20/20#2008 tournament|2008 tournament]]. They played two matches in the tournament,<ref name="T20M">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Teams/3/3021/Twenty20_Matches.html|title=Twenty20 Matches played by United States Virgin Islands|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> one a preliminary round victory against [[St Kitts cricket team|St Kitts]] by 4 wickets,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/124/124444.html|title=St Kitts v United States Virgin Islands, 2007/08 Stanford 20/20|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> before losing in the first round to [[Antigua and Barbuda national cricket team|Antigua and Barbuda]] by 24 runs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/124/124451.html|title=Antigua and Barbuda v United States Virgin Islands, 2007/08 Stanford 20/20|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> The United States Virgin Islands would have taken part in a further tournament to be played in 2009, however its creator [[Allen Stanford]] was charged with fraud and arrested in June 2009, bringing an end to the competition. The tournament was then replaced by the [[Caribbean Twenty20]], with only first-class teams allowed to take part.{{#tag:ref|The first-class domestic teams in the West Indies are: [[Barbados national cricket team|Barbados]], [[Combined Campuses and Colleges cricket team|Combined Campuses and Colleges]], [[Guyana national cricket team|Guyana]], [[Jamaica national cricket team|Jamaica]], [[Leeward Islands cricket team|Leeward Islands]], [[Trinidad and Tobago national cricket team|Trinidad and Tobago]] and [[Windward Islands cricket team|Windward Islands]].|group=n}}

In total, the United States Virgin Islands played four Twenty20 matches, all at the [[Stanford Cricket Ground]],<ref name="T20M"/> with ten players playing in all four matches.<ref name="APPS"/> [[Sherville Huggins]] scored more runs than any other Virgin Islander with 126,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/batting/most_runs_career.html?class=6;id=47;type=team|title=Records / United States Virgin Islands / Twenty20 matches / Most runs|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> with him also making the highest individual score of 51 against Saint Maarten, also making him the only Virgin Islander to pass [[half century|fifty]] runs in an innings.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/batting/most_runs_innings.html?class=6;id=47;type=team|title=Records / United States Virgin Islands / Twenty20 matches / High scores|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> [[Calvin Lewis]] and [[Dane Weston]] have both claimed 6 wickets in Twenty20 matches, more than any other Virgin Islander, however of the two, Lewis has the better [[bowling average]] of 8.66.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/most_wickets_career.html?class=6;id=47;type=team|title=Records / United States Virgin Islands / Twenty20 matches / Most wickets|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> Lewis' figures of 3/16 against Antigua and Barbuda are the best bowling figures by a Virgin Islander.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/bowling/best_figures_innings.html?class=6;id=47;type=team|title=Records / United States Virgin Islands / Twenty20 matches / Best bowling figures in an innings|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> Huggins [[captain (cricket)|captained]] the team in all four matches,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/individual/list_captains.html?class=6;id=47;type=team|title=Records / United States Virgin Islands / Twenty20 matches / List of captains|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref> while [[Alderman Lesmond]] was the teams [[wicket-keeper]] in all four matches it played.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/keeping/most_dismissals_career.html?class=6;id=47;type=team|title=Records / United States Virgin Islands / Twenty20 matches / Most dismissals|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=6 January 2013}}</ref>

This list includes all players who have played at least one Twenty20 match and is initially arranged in the order of debut appearance. Where more than one player won their first cap in the same match, those players are initially listed alphabetically at the time of debut.

